'cont'=>'(Jiashen July third), August 21, 1944, the opening of the Dumbarton Oaks Conference. after outbreak of the <br> World War II, the League of Nations as an international organization actually exists in name only. After consultations, the Soviet Union, the United States, Britain, August 21 to October 7 in 1944, held in the Washington suburb of Georgetown Dumbarton Oaks Building Conference. Meeting points in the United States, Soviet Union, Britain (August 21 to September 28) and two stages in the United States, Britain (September 29). After the talks, the meeting adopted a motion on the establishment of a universal international organization, and suggested that this organization be called the \"United Nations\". The bill provides that the organization and terms of reference of the purposes and principles of the United Nations, the General Assembly of the United Nations Security Council, the Secretariat and other major institutions, as well as the maintenance of international peace and security and on international economic and social cooperation in various arrangements. In the second stage of the meeting in addition to agreeing the motion of the previous stage, add three points important recommendations: 1, on the peaceful settlement of disputes, the international organizations should give due consideration to the principles of justice and international law; 2, the General Assembly should bear the codification and development of international law task; 3, the Economic and Social Council should be expanded to the education and cultural cooperation. China&#39;s proposal has made the United States and Britain Soviet Union endorses. The meeting of the permanent members of the veto power of the Security Council, on the eligibility of the founding Member States there are differences, but it passed the motion to be prepared by the San Francisco Conference in 1945, the basis of the Charter of the United Nations. <br>'
